@startuml errors
title Failure paths — every failure is a one-frame ERROR answer
hide footbox
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Coordinator" as C
participant "Node" as N

== Load-time errors ==

C -> N : LOAD_MODULE (module already loaded)
N --> C : ERROR [BUSY]
note right of C : unload first — loading over\na loaded module is rejected

C -> N : LOAD_MODULE, len > CONFIG_WASP_MAX_MODULE_SIZE
note over N : network handler **drains** the oversized\nframe — stream sync is never lost
N --> C : ERROR [TOO_LARGE]

C -> N : LOAD_MODULE [invalid wasm, or imports\noutside the ""wasp"" namespace]
N --> C : ERROR [LOAD_FAILED, WAMR's diagnostic text]

== Call-time errors ==

C -> N : CALL "fib" (nothing loaded)
N --> C : ERROR [NO_MODULE]

C -> N : CALL "gdc" (typo / missing export_name)
N --> C : ERROR [NO_FUNC "gdc"]

C -> N : CALL "fib" — wrong argc, or the\nC signature isn't all-i32
N --> C : ERROR [BAD_ARGS, detail]

C -> N : CALL "boom" — module hits ""unreachable"",\nOOB access, __builtin_trap(), remote segfault…
N --> C : ERROR [TRAP, exception text]
note over N
  The sandbox holds: the module stays
  loaded, the node is unharmed, and
  the next CALL works.
end note

== Stream desync ==

C -> N : bytes that don't start 'W' 'A'
note over N : bad magic means the stream is\ndesynchronized — unrecoverable
N --> C : TCP close
note right of C : reconnect and start over\nwith HELLO
@enduml
